instructions:
    1. Before use, it is necessary to enable PWM in the kernel
        The specific path is: Device Drivers → Pulse Width Modulation (PWM) Support
        Device tree enablement: arch/mips/boot/dts/industrial/PRJ007.dtsi
            Need to modify the PWM device node to okay
    2.When enabling, it is necessary to pay attention to whether the GPIO used in the PWM channel is the same as that used in the development board
        <*>   Ingenic PWM support
        PWM channel0 GPIO select (PWM channel0 PB17)  --->
    3. Usage: (For example, using 0 channel, cycle 10000, duty cycle 5000, default polarity)
        ./pwm_test.sh 0 10000 5000 0
        The first parameter represents the PWM channel
        The second parameter represents the PWM cycle
        The third parameter represents the PWM duty cycle
        The fourth parameter represents the use of polarity, with 0 indicating the default polarity and 1 indicating polarity reversal
        If the script is used directly, the output will be generated by default

Precautions for use:
1. Open up to 3 channels simultaneously during use
2. It is possible to use without inputting parameters or without inputting polarity when inputting parameters
